OL,3,CWomen's Six Nations: Wales lose 62-24
OL,4,Cto England
OL,6,FMeg Jones and Marlie Packer both
OL,7,Fscored twice as world champions
OL,8,FEngland ran in 10 tries in a 62-24
OL,9,FWomen's Six Nations demolition of
OL,10,FWales.
OL,12,FMaddie Feaunati, debutant Millie
OL,13,FDavid, Amy Cokayne, Claudia Moloney-
OL,14,FMacDonald, Jess Breach and Maud Muir
OL,15,Falso went over at Ashton Gate, with
OL,16,FKeira Bevan, Kelsey Jones, Bethan
OL,17,FLewis and Seren Lockwood replying as
OL,18,FJohn Mitchell's table-toppers extended
OL,19,Ftheir 100 per cent record in the
OL,20,Ftournament with a third win.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G1/6
