FL,467,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F466A1777306270
OL,3,CWomen's Six Nations: Wales lose 62-24
OL,4,Cto England
OL,6,FTo their credit, Wales stayed in the
OL,7,Fgame and quickly reduced the deficit
OL,8,Fwhen scrum-half Bevan picked up from
OL,9,Fthe base of the ruck and went through
OL,10,Fa gap, converting her own try to make
OL,11,Fit 12-7.
OL,13,FHowever, flanker Packer was driven
OL,14,Fover before centre Jones scored a fine
OL,15,Fsolo effort to claim the bonus point
OL,16,Fwith Rowland successful from her first
OL,17,Fattempt, although Welsh hooker Jones
OL,18,Falso crossed from a well-worked line-
OL,19,Fout move.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G3/6
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,467,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F466A1777306270
OL,3,CWomen's Six Nations: Wales lose 62-24
OL,4,Cto England
OL,6,FBut the Red Roses went in at the break
OL,7,Fwith a 29-12 lead after Jones started
OL,8,Fand finished a thrilling attack
OL,9,Finvolving winger Moloney-MacDonald and
OL,10,FEllie Kildunne.
OL,12,FEngland picked up where they had left
OL,13,Foff when hooker Cokayne peeled off the
OL,14,Fback of a rolling maul to touch down
OL,15,Fwith Rowland adding the two points,
OL,16,Fand the visitors' hopes were dealt a
OL,17,Ffurther blow when full-back Kayleigh
OL,18,FPowell was yellow-carded for a
OL,19,Fdeliberate knock-on.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G4/6
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,467,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F466A1777306270
OL,3,CWomen's Six Nations: Wales lose 62-24
OL,4,Cto England
OL,6,FMoloney-MacDonald took full advantage
OL,7,Falmost immediately with a fine finish
OL,8,Fin the corner, and Breach scored her
OL,9,Fside's eighth, converted by fellow
OL,10,Freplacement Zoe Harrison before
OL,11,FPowell's return.
OL,13,FTries from Packer and Muir either side
OL,14,Fof Wales flanker Lewis' effort ` both
OL,15,Fof which were converted by Harrison `
OL,16,Ftook England's tally to 10, but
OL,17,FLockwood had the final say to snatch a
OL,18,Fbonus point for the visitors with the
OL,19,Fclock in the red.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G5/6
